      "slug": "html-main-content-element",
      "title": "HTML Main Content Element",
      "description": "The main element marks the dominant, unique content of a page and must appear only once per document.",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": [
            {
              "value": "The "
            },
            {
              "value": "<main>",
              "bold": true,
              "highlight": true,
              "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/main"
            },
            {
              "value": " element identifies the "
            },
            {
              "value": "primary content region",
              "bold": true
            },
            {
              "value": " of a page: the content that is unique to this page and not repeated across the site. Navigation, headers, footers, and sidebars are excluded. There must be "
            },
            {
              "value": "exactly one visible main element",
              "bold": true
            },
            {
              "value": " per page at any given time. A page may contain additional "
            },
            {
              "value": "<main>",
              "bold": true,
              "highlight": true
            },
            {
              "value": " elements only if they carry the "
            },
            {
              "value": "hidden",
              "bold": true,
              "highlight": true,
              "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Global_attributes/hidden"
            },
            {
              "value": " attribute, a pattern used in single-page applications to pre-render inactive views. The "
            },
            {
              "value": "<main>",
              "bold": true,
              "highlight": true
            },
            {
              "value": " element maps directly to the "
            },
            {
              "value": "ARIA main landmark role",
              "bold": true,
              "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/main_role"
            },
            {
              "value": ", giving assistive technology users a direct jump target to skip past repeated navigation."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "variant": "warning",
          "title": "Do not nest main inside other landmarks",
          "text": "The main element must not be a descendant of article, aside, footer, header, or nav. It should be a direct child of body or a generic div wrapper, never nested inside another sectioning element."
        }
      ],
      "examples": [
        {
          "title": "main Element with Skip Navigation Link",
          "description": "Demonstrates the main element paired with a skip navigation link, the most common accessibility pattern used alongside main to let keyboard and screen reader users bypass repeated header content.",
          "code_snippet": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n  <head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\" />\n    <title>Main Element Example</title>\n    <style>\n      /* Skip link is visually hidden but appears on keyboard focus */\n      .skip-link {\n        position: absolute;\n        top: -100%;\n        left: 0;\n        background: #000;\n        color: #fff;\n        padding: 0.5rem 1rem;\n        z-index: 9999;\n        text-decoration: none;\n      }\n      .skip-link:focus { top: 0; }\n      header { background: #222; color: white; padding: 1rem 2rem; }\n      nav a { color: white; margin-right: 1rem; }\n      main { padding: 2rem; }\n    </style>\n  </head>\n  <body>\n    <!-- Skip link must be the very first focusable element on the page -->\n    <a class=\"skip-link\" href=\"#main-content\">Skip to main content</a>\n    <header>\n      <nav aria-label=\"Primary\">\n        <a href=\"/\">Home</a>\n        <a href=\"/products\">Products</a>\n        <a href=\"/contact\">Contact</a>\n      </nav>\n    </header>\n    <!-- id matches the skip link href -->\n    <!-- tabindex=\"-1\" lets the element receive programmatic focus -->\n    <main id=\"main-content\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n      <h1>Our Products</h1>\n      <p>Browse our full range of developer tools and services.</p>\n    </main>\n  </body>\n</html>",
          "output": "The page renders a dark header with three navigation links followed by the main content area showing the heading 'Our Products' and a paragraph. When a keyboard user presses Tab as their first action, a 'Skip to main content' link appears at the top of the page. Activating it moves focus directly to the main element, bypassing the navigation entirely.",
          "images": null,
          "video_url": null
        }
      ],
      "image_banner_url": null,
      "images": null,
      "video_url": null,
      "when_to_use": [],
      "when_to_avoid": [],
      "what_it_solves": [],
      "conceptual_understanding": [
        {
          "text": [
            {
              "value": "The "
            },
            {
              "value": "<main>",
              "bold": true,
              "highlight": true,
              "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/main"
            },
            {
              "value": " element is the main stage at a concert venue. Everything else, the entrance, the bar, the cloakroom, exists to support the experience, but the stage is why people came. Screen readers let users teleport directly to the stage and skip the lobby."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "text": [
            {
              "value": "Using a skip link with "
            },
            {
              "value": "<main>",
              "bold": true,
              "highlight": true,
              "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/main"
            },
            {
              "value": " is like the express elevator in a tall office building. Regular visitors tab through every "
            },
            {
              "value": "<nav>",
              "bold": true,
              "highlight": true,
              "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/nav"
            },
            {
              "value": " link, but the express elevator takes you straight to the floor you need in one move."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "common_mistakes": [],
      "bonus_tips": [
        {
          "text": [
            {
              "value": "Add "
            },
            {
              "value": "tabindex=\"-1\"",
              "bold": true,
              "highlight": true,
              "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Global_attributes/tabindex"
            },
            {
              "value": " to your "
            },
            {
              "value": "<main>",
              "bold": true,
              "highlight": true,
              "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/main"
            },
            {
              "value": " whenever you use a skip link pointing to it. Without this attribute, some browsers move visual focus but not keyboard focus, leaving keyboard-only users stranded at the top of the document."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
